					<description><![CDATA[We look back over 02025: where we spent our time and money. This annual report is meant as a guide for others to use as a benchmark for themselves.]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Each year we put together an overview of the status of the company. It is less about the exact numbers, and more about how and where we spend our time and money. The company continues to evolve. You can read any of our previous <a href="https://optional.is/required/category/annual-report/">Annual Reports</a>.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These are meant to be a guide for others who might be starting out or struggling. We&#8217;re definitely not the &#8220;best&#8221; or &#8220;right&#8221; way to run a company. We&#8217;re a small, digital company, if you are too, then knowing where your money is going compared to others can be helpful.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Finances</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">We exported all our invoices from the bookkeeping software and much like everything, we&#8217;re pretty steady. We&#8217;re sending ~1.5 invoices a month. One invoice is our retainer, the others are additional projects, usually in Australia, sometimes Iceland or the UK.</p>



